### HOW to RUN files in your local 
## After downloading the files, first run Redisin your local machine with the following command:
# docker run -d --name redis -p 6379:6379 redis

# Then write the commands
pnpm install 
pnpm dev


#################### IN POSTMAN ############################
# Send requests to the server to fetch user data Implement a GET /users/:id endpoint

GET http://localhost:5000/users/1
GET http://localhost:5000/users/2
GET http://localhost:5000/users/3

the result like:
{
    "fromCache": true, // if from Cache 
    "user": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "John Doe",
        "email": "john@example.com"
    }
}


# or
{
    "fromCache": false, // if not from Cache 
    "user": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "John Doe",
        "email": "john@example.com"
    }
}

# Send a request to the server to check the status Cache Status: Implement a GET /cache-status endpoint
GET http://localhost:5000/cache-status


# Send a request to the server to clear the Cache DELETE: Implement a DELETE /cache endpoint
DELETE http://localhost:5000/cache



# if you send to many requests the rateLimiter middeleware will prevent you form sending 
#  it is a burst traffic handling. Allow 
# a maximum of 10 requests per minute, with a burst capacity of 5 requests in a 10-second 